# Scenario: Multiple filters in 'where'
# Why: Ensures the compiler correctly handles multiple keys in the 'where' object and maps various operators (_lt, _gte, _lte) to RQL.
query 'CALL graphql::explain("query { transactions(where: { blockNumber_lt: 50, index_gte: 1, status: true }) { hash } }")'
---
> +-------+----------+--------------------+
> |  idx  |   kind   |       detail       |
> +-------+----------+--------------------+
> |   0   |   From   |    transactions    |
> |   1   |  Filter  |  blockNumber < 50  |
> |   2   |  Filter  |     index >= 1     |
> |   3   |  Filter  |   status == true   |
> |   4   |   Map    |        hash        |
> +-------+----------+--------------------+
>
